==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Midriff
<hw>Mid"riff</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧d"r⟦icr⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>midhrif</ets>; <ets>midd</ets> mid, middle + <ets>hrif</ets>
bowels, womb; akin to OFries. <ets>midref</ets> midriff, <ets>rif</ets>,
<ets>ref</ets>, belly, OHG. <ets>href</ets> body, and to L.
<ets>corpus</ets> body. See <er>Corpse</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>See <er>Diaphragm</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The middle part of the front of the body, from the
waist to the chest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Smote him into the <qex>midriff</qex> with a stone.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That part of a garment, especially a dress or
bodice, that covers the midriff{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mid-sea</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Mid sea</ent>⟦br⟧
